<%- include('partials/head', {
  title,
  metaTitle,
  metaDescription,
  canonicalPath
}) %>

<%- include('partials/header') %>

<%
  const s = settings || {};
  const phoneRaw = String(s.phone || "").trim();
  const phoneTel = phoneRaw.replace(/\s+/g, "");
%>

<div class="wrap">
  <div class="card">
    <h1 style="color: var(--accent);">Truck Hearse FAQ</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Answers to common questions about truck hearse hire, lorry hearse hire, alternative funeral transport,
      and our specialist hearses available across the UK mainland.
    </p>

    <div class="cta" style="margin:18px 0 8px;">
      <a class="btn" href="/contact">Enquire</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/gallery">View gallery</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/case-studies">Case studies</a>
      <% if (phoneTel) { %>
        <a class="btn" href="tel:<%= phoneTel %>">Call <%= phoneRaw %></a>
      <% } %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">What is a truck hearse?</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        A truck hearse is an alternative funeral vehicle based on a heavy goods vehicle or large truck,
        adapted and presented for funeral use. It offers funeral directors and families a distinctive and
        respectful alternative to a traditional hearse, especially where the person being remembered had
        a strong connection to haulage, transport, engineering, mechanics, HGVs or road life.
      </p>
      <p>
        For many families, a truck hearse creates a final journey that feels more personal and meaningful
        than a standard funeral vehicle. It can reflect a loved one’s career, interests or identity while
        still maintaining dignity, professionalism and presence on the day of the funeral.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">What is the difference between a truck hearse and a traditional hearse?</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        A traditional hearse is usually a purpose-built funeral vehicle in the familiar style seen at most funerals.
        A truck hearse or lorry hearse provides a more individual alternative. Both can be respectful and suitable
        for a funeral, but a truck hearse is typically chosen when families want the final journey to reflect a life
        connected to haulage, transport, engineering or a love of large vehicles.
      </p>
      <p>
        The difference is not about reducing dignity or professionalism. It is about creating a more personal tribute.
        Where a traditional hearse offers convention, a truck hearse offers individuality. For some funerals,
        that difference is exactly what makes the day feel right.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-bottom:0;">
        You can also read more on our
        <a href="/truck-hearse-vs-traditional-hearse">truck hearse vs traditional hearse</a> page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">Do you offer truck hearse and lorry hearse hire across the UK?</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        Yes. We offer specialist truck hearse and lorry hearse hire across the UK mainland, subject to date,
        location and vehicle availability. We are based near Chester, close to North Wales and North West England,
        but can provide specialist funeral transport much further afield depending on the arrangements.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-bottom:0;">
        For more on UK coverage, see our
        <a href="/lorry-hearse-hire-uk">lorry hearse hire across the UK</a> page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">Who usually chooses a truck hearse for a funeral?</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        A truck hearse is often chosen for someone with a strong connection to trucking, haulage, transport,
        recovery, heavy vehicles, mechanics, engineering, agriculture or life on the road. It may also be chosen
        simply because the family wants the final journey to feel more personal than a standard funeral vehicle.
      </p>
      <p>
        For many families, the vehicle becomes part of the tribute itself, helping the funeral feel more individual,
        memorable and fitting for the person being remembered.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">Is a truck hearse still respectful for a funeral?</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        Yes. A truck hearse is chosen to add personality and meaning to the final journey while maintaining
        a respectful, dignified and professional presentation. The aim is not novelty for its own sake,
        but a tribute that feels more relevant and personal for the family and for the life being honoured.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">Which specialist vehicles do you offer?</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        We currently offer the <a href="/renault-magnum-hearse">Renault Magnum truck hearse</a> and the
        <a href="/erf-ec12-hearse">ERF EC12 lorry hearse</a>. Each vehicle has its own character, appearance
        and presence, and each may suit a funeral in a slightly different way.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-bottom:0;">
        You can view both on our <a href="/gallery">gallery page</a> and read more about them on their
        individual vehicle pages.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">Do you work directly with families or through funeral directors?</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        Our specialist hearses are supplied exclusively for the funeral profession, and in many cases the booking
        will be arranged through the funeral director handling the funeral. Families are also welcome to contact us
        directly to discuss availability, vehicle choice and whether one of our hearses may be suitable for the service.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">What information should I include in an enquiry?</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        The most useful details are the funeral date if known, the general service location, and which vehicle you are
        interested in if that is already clear. If you are unsure whether the Renault Magnum or ERF EC12 is the better fit,
        we can help guide that decision.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-bottom:0;">
        You can enquire through our <a href="/contact">contact page</a> or by phone.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">Can I see examples of completed services?</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        Yes. Our <a href="/case-studies">case studies</a> page includes recent field updates and completed service
        examples showing our specialist hearses out in real funeral work. These updates help show how alternative
        funeral transport can still be dignified, reliable and professionally delivered.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-bottom:0;">
        You can also explore images and videos on our <a href="/gallery">gallery</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">Frequently asked questions</h2>

    <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Do you offer truck hearse hire across the UK?</h3>
    <p>
      Yes. We offer truck hearse and lorry hearse hire across the UK mainland, subject to date, location and vehicle availability.
    </p>

    <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Who chooses a lorry hearse for a funeral?</h3>
    <p>
      Lorry hearse hire is often chosen for someone with a connection to trucking, haulage, transport, engineering, mechanics,
      road life or heavy vehicles. It is also chosen by families who want a unique and personal final journey.
    </p>

    <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Is a truck hearse still respectful for a funeral?</h3>
    <p>
      Yes. A truck hearse is chosen to add personality and meaning to the funeral while maintaining a respectful,
      dignified and professional presentation.
    </p>

    <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Which vehicles do you currently offer?</h3>
    <p>
      We currently offer the Renault Magnum truck hearse and the ERF EC12 lorry hearse.
    </p>

    <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">How do I enquire about availability?</h3>
    <p>
      You can enquire through our contact page or by phone to discuss the date, location and the type of specialist hearse required.
    </p>

    <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Can you help if I am not sure which vehicle is the better fit?</h3>
    <p>
      Yes. We can help you decide whether the Renault Magnum or ERF EC12 is likely to be the more suitable vehicle for the funeral.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title">Explore more</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p><a href="/truck-hearse-vs-traditional-hearse">Truck hearse vs traditional hearse</a></p>
      <p><a href="/lorry-hearse-hire-uk">Lorry hearse hire across the UK</a></p>
      <p><a href="/renault-magnum-hearse">Renault Magnum truck hearse</a></p>
      <p><a href="/erf-ec12-hearse">ERF EC12 lorry hearse</a></p>
      <p><a href="/case-studies">Truck hearse case studies</a></p>
      <p><a href="/gallery">Photo gallery</a></p>
      <p><a href="/contact">Get a quote</a></p>
      <p><a href="/">Back to home</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
